1
00:00:06,005 --> 00:00:08,738
- [whooshes]
- [tires screech]

2
00:00:10,871 --> 00:00:12,905
READY OR NOT: TEXAS

3
00:00:12,971 --> 00:00:16,905
AFTERNOON OF DAY 5,
A HOUSTON DEPARTMENT STORE

4
00:00:19,671 --> 00:00:22,271
ENJOYING CHICKEN DURING A QUICK BREAK

5
00:00:22,338 --> 00:00:24,138
MUNCHING

6
00:00:24,205 --> 00:00:27,005
- The chicken tastes amazing.
- [Woo-jung] It is.

7
00:00:27,071 --> 00:00:28,905
- [Yung-suk] You think so?
- It's really tender.

8
00:00:28,971 --> 00:00:30,571
[Yung-suk] That's what they're known for.

9
00:00:30,638 --> 00:00:32,038
[Woo-jung] I want a bit more.

10
00:00:32,105 --> 00:00:34,971
- [Dae-ju] No, we have to go to Benihana.
- You have to resist.

11
00:00:35,038 --> 00:00:36,438
TODAY'S DINNER
TEPPANYAKI RESTAURANT BENIHANA

12
00:00:36,505 --> 00:00:37,971
ONE OF SEO-JIN'S
FAVORITE PLACES TO EAT IN COLLEGE

13
00:00:38,038 --> 00:00:41,171
[Woo-jung] It's like
a trip down memory lane for you.

14
00:00:41,238 --> 00:00:42,438
[Yung-suk] It's been 30 years.

15
00:00:42,505 --> 00:00:44,638
- [Yung-suk] No, it's been nearly 40 years.
- Trust me.

16
00:00:44,705 --> 00:00:46,771
We're in the city right now.

17
00:00:46,838 --> 00:00:49,405
But if you go to the suburbs,

18
00:00:49,471 --> 00:00:52,738
Benihana is the best place to eat.

19
00:00:52,805 --> 00:00:54,971
The locals go there for their birthdays.

20
00:00:55,038 --> 00:00:58,338
Going to Benihana is a special event.

21
00:00:58,405 --> 00:01:00,538
It's a special treat.

22
00:01:00,605 --> 00:01:01,871
If you see the menu,

23
00:01:02,605 --> 00:01:05,271
they have meat,
but you can also just go for seafood.

24
00:01:05,338 --> 00:01:06,438
[Woo-jung] I love that.

25
00:01:06,505 --> 00:01:09,071
I don't usually go for the meat.

26
00:01:09,138 --> 00:01:10,705
[Yung-suk] Is there shrimp?

27
00:01:10,771 --> 00:01:12,771
- Lobster--
- [Woo-jung] Is there shrimp or octopus?

28
00:01:12,838 --> 00:01:15,005
They offer things like lobster and shrimp.

29
00:01:15,071 --> 00:01:17,405
The portions are quite small.

30
00:01:18,171 --> 00:01:19,871
You get to try a variety.

31
00:01:19,938 --> 00:01:23,538
SETTING OUT WITH RAISED EXPECTATIONS

32
00:01:26,371 --> 00:01:28,138
SCANNING NERVOUSLY

33
00:01:28,205 --> 00:01:29,905
Why do you look so nervous?

34
00:01:29,971 --> 00:01:31,971
- Don't be nervous.
- [Dae-ju] Okay.

35
00:01:32,038 --> 00:01:34,205
Once that car goes,
should I turn that way?

36
00:01:34,705 --> 00:01:35,538
What?

37
00:01:35,605 --> 00:01:37,138
- You can only turn one way.
- This way?

38
00:01:37,205 --> 00:01:38,271
There's no other way.

39
00:01:38,338 --> 00:01:40,238
- [Seo-jin] Do what you like.
- The exit's on the right.

40
00:01:40,305 --> 00:01:41,138
Okay.

41
00:01:41,205 --> 00:01:43,105
How do I turn the blinker on?

42
00:01:43,171 --> 00:01:44,871
You don't know?

43
00:01:44,938 --> 00:01:46,905
- It's usually here, right?
- Yes.

44
00:01:46,971 --> 00:01:48,971
- [Yung-suk laughs]
- [laughs] It's fine.

45
00:01:49,038 --> 00:01:50,938
You don't need to worry.

46
00:01:51,605 --> 00:01:54,505
[Yung-suk] <i>♪ It's raining, it's raining… ♪</i>

47
00:01:54,571 --> 00:01:55,705
[Seo-jin] What song is that?

48
00:01:55,771 --> 00:01:57,238
- [Dae-ju] It's made up.
- [Woo-jung] He made it up.

49
00:01:57,805 --> 00:02:01,605
Let's read about Benihana on Wikipedia.

50
00:02:02,605 --> 00:02:06,305
It says Benihana means "red flower."

51
00:02:07,071 --> 00:02:08,005
[Dae-ju] "Red flower"?

52
00:02:08,071 --> 00:02:09,838
"Hana" is Japanese for "flower."

53
00:02:09,905 --> 00:02:12,305
- [Dae-ju] It's "red flower."
- [Yung-suk] Yes.

54
00:02:12,371 --> 00:02:14,571
It expanded to the US in 1964.

55
00:02:14,638 --> 00:02:15,738
[Dae-ju] Oh, goodness.

56
00:02:16,238 --> 00:02:17,805
MEANWHILE BENIHANA IS DRAWING CLOSER

57
00:02:17,871 --> 00:02:19,671
[Dae-ju] We're finally almost there.

58
00:02:19,738 --> 00:02:20,738
Look at that.

59
00:02:20,805 --> 00:02:23,605
It looks like an authentic Japanese house.

60
00:02:23,671 --> 00:02:26,171
- [Woo-jung] It does.
- [Yung-suk] I see what they're going for.

61
00:02:26,238 --> 00:02:27,605
A PERFECTLY ON-THEME RESTAURANT

62
00:02:28,171 --> 00:02:33,471
BENIHANA, A JAPANESE TEPPANYAKI RESTAURANT

63
00:02:34,171 --> 00:02:38,005
THE CHEFS PREPARE THE MEALS
BEFORE YOUR EYES

64
00:02:38,071 --> 00:02:42,238
AND PUT ON SPECIAL PERFORMANCES

65
00:02:42,305 --> 00:02:46,338
EXCLUSIVE TO BENIHANA

66
00:02:46,405 --> 00:02:48,971
[Woo-jung] Is it normal
to have this many griddles?

67
00:02:49,038 --> 00:02:51,838
- Right?
- You get one or two fancy griddles.

68
00:02:51,905 --> 00:02:53,938
But this place is for the masses.

69
00:02:54,005 --> 00:02:57,471
I've never seen a setup
like this at a Teppanyaki restaurant.

70
00:02:57,538 --> 00:02:59,338
We don't have places like this in Korea.

71
00:02:59,405 --> 00:03:01,171
This place is very open and casual.

72
00:03:02,271 --> 00:03:04,105
[staff in English]
<i>♪ Happy birthday to you ♪</i>

73
00:03:04,171 --> 00:03:05,571
[in Korean] That surprised me.

74
00:03:05,638 --> 00:03:08,271
[staff continues singing in English]

75
00:03:08,338 --> 00:03:11,438
[in Korean] Told you they did that here.

76
00:03:11,505 --> 00:03:12,705
[Woo-jung] They're celebrating right now.

77
00:03:12,771 --> 00:03:14,038
PEOPLE CELEBRATE
THEIR BIRTHDAYS AT BENIHANA

78
00:03:14,105 --> 00:03:17,071
CELEBRATING BEING PROVEN RIGHT

79
00:03:17,705 --> 00:03:20,105
- [Yung-suk] Their signature drink.
- [server in English] There you go.

80
00:03:20,171 --> 00:03:22,338
- Thank you.
- [Woo-jung in Korean] Are you two sharing?

81
00:03:22,405 --> 00:03:23,438
DAMN IT

82
00:03:23,505 --> 00:03:25,871
[Dae-ju] I guess you look good together.

83
00:03:25,938 --> 00:03:27,838
Have a drink, honey.

84
00:03:27,905 --> 00:03:28,738
HATING THIS

85
00:03:28,805 --> 00:03:29,805
[Woo-jung] That's so…

86
00:03:29,871 --> 00:03:31,705
TAKE A SIP

87
00:03:31,771 --> 00:03:33,405
Don't touch it with your hands.

88
00:03:33,471 --> 00:03:34,738
Go wash your hands.

89
00:03:34,805 --> 00:03:36,971
I saw you lick your fingers
while eating chicken.

90
00:03:37,038 --> 00:03:38,038
Go wash them.

91
00:03:38,105 --> 00:03:40,771
- Let's go wash our hands.
- [laughs]

92
00:03:40,838 --> 00:03:42,171
Oh, come on.

93
00:03:42,238 --> 00:03:44,738
It's so annoying.
He's making me wash my hands.

94
00:03:44,805 --> 00:03:45,671
A MOMENT LATER…

95
00:03:45,738 --> 00:03:47,271
[in English] It's so clean.

96
00:03:50,238 --> 00:03:53,705
BACK AT THE TABLE FEELING FRESH

97
00:03:53,771 --> 00:03:56,871
[Woo-jung in Korean] We should do this.
Whose birthday is coming up?

98
00:03:56,938 --> 00:03:58,271
Who has a birthday in April?

99
00:03:58,338 --> 00:03:59,671
[gasps] Oh my God.

100
00:03:59,738 --> 00:04:01,538
We should celebrate it.

101
00:04:01,605 --> 00:04:03,071
Did you not know my birthday?

102
00:04:03,138 --> 00:04:04,405
- It's in April?
- I'm hurt.

103
00:04:04,471 --> 00:04:05,971
[Woo-jung] It's so soon.

104
00:04:06,038 --> 00:04:08,205
- Isn't it next week?
- It is.

105
00:04:08,271 --> 00:04:09,238
On what date?

106
00:04:09,305 --> 00:04:10,438
It's the 15th.

107
00:04:10,505 --> 00:04:12,571
Oh, good. You'll be back in Korea.

108
00:04:12,638 --> 00:04:14,405
[laughs] Why is that good?

109
00:04:14,471 --> 00:04:16,871
- It's good we won't be together.
- [both laugh]

110
00:04:16,938 --> 00:04:19,571
Wish me a happy birthday from afar.

111
00:04:19,638 --> 00:04:21,171
FEELING HURT

112
00:04:21,238 --> 00:04:23,338
EATING SALAD FIRST
TO PREVENT A SUGAR SPIKE

113
00:04:23,404 --> 00:04:26,038
- [Dae-ju] The dressing is a bit different.
- [Woo-jung] It's nice.

114
00:04:26,538 --> 00:04:30,705
Has anyone filmed Benihana in the US?

115
00:04:30,771 --> 00:04:32,738
- [Yung-suk] It's the first time.
- [Woo-jung] I believe so.

116
00:04:32,805 --> 00:04:33,871
PROUD TO BE THE FIRST

117
00:04:33,938 --> 00:04:37,705
When they perform later,
we need to film them closely.

118
00:04:38,571 --> 00:04:42,071
Don't they make drawings with eggs?

119
00:04:42,138 --> 00:04:44,338
They spin the egg like this.

120
00:04:44,405 --> 00:04:47,571
- They spin it like crazy, then throw it.
- [Woo-jung] That's right.

121
00:04:47,638 --> 00:04:49,605
Then they crack it as it lands.

122
00:04:49,671 --> 00:04:51,405
- [chef in English] Hello.
- [Yung-suk] Hello.

123
00:04:51,471 --> 00:04:52,738
- Hello.
- [Seo-jin] Hi.

124
00:04:58,405 --> 00:05:00,238
- Oh, yes.
- Yes, first time.

125
00:05:01,205 --> 00:05:02,138
[clanging]

126
00:05:03,671 --> 00:05:05,471
Ready.

127
00:05:05,538 --> 00:05:07,338
BILLY IS IN THE ZONE

128
00:05:07,405 --> 00:05:09,505
- [Yung-suk in Korean] Look at that.
- [crew chuckling]

129
00:05:09,571 --> 00:05:12,905
SURPRISINGLY INTO THIS KIND OF THING

130
00:05:12,971 --> 00:05:14,671
KNIVES SWISHING

131
00:05:15,338 --> 00:05:17,905
- [cheering]
- [Billy in English] Thank you.

132
00:05:17,971 --> 00:05:19,871
[in Korean] I liked
that Wakanda-style greeting.

133
00:05:19,938 --> 00:05:21,005
[in English]

134
00:05:22,105 --> 00:05:23,005
[Seo-jin] Yes.

135
00:05:31,671 --> 00:05:34,605
- [Yung-suk and Woo-jung] Yes.
- We got the egg roll.

136
00:05:34,671 --> 00:05:36,138
BOUNCE

137
00:05:36,205 --> 00:05:37,538
PERFECT CATCH!

138
00:05:37,605 --> 00:05:40,171
- [in Korean] That's it.
- That's the stuff.

139
00:05:40,238 --> 00:05:41,738
- Oh, wow.
- It's so good.

140
00:05:41,805 --> 00:05:43,905
AS EVERYBODY ENJOYS THE SHOW

141
00:05:43,971 --> 00:05:45,205
- [Yung-suk] This is it.
- [Woo-jung] Is it?

142
00:05:45,271 --> 00:05:46,438
HIS DIMPLES DEEPEN WITH PRIDE

143
00:05:48,505 --> 00:05:51,671
- [Yung-suk] What? Ice cream?
- [Billy speaks in English]

144
00:05:51,738 --> 00:05:53,871
[in Korean] It's pistachio ice cream.

145
00:05:53,938 --> 00:05:56,971
Benihana works hard to develop new menus.

146
00:05:57,538 --> 00:05:59,705
[Woo-jung] This is so much fun.

147
00:05:59,771 --> 00:06:01,438
Is it really ice cream?

148
00:06:01,505 --> 00:06:03,005
- I don't think so.
- Is it butter?

149
00:06:03,071 --> 00:06:04,271
[Billy in English]
This is special ice cream.

150
00:06:05,805 --> 00:06:07,238
[Yung-suk in Korean] Oh, I see.

151
00:06:07,305 --> 00:06:09,038
[Billy in English]
We call it our special ice cream.

152
00:06:09,105 --> 00:06:10,371
[Dae-ju] Oh, ice cream.

153
00:06:10,438 --> 00:06:11,771
- [Yung-suk in Korean] Garlic butter?
- [Dae-ju] Yes.

154
00:06:11,838 --> 00:06:13,238
[Yung-suk] I knew it.

155
00:06:13,305 --> 00:06:14,705
[in English]

156
00:06:14,771 --> 00:06:16,405
[Yung-suk in Korean]
They serve the fried rice first?

157
00:06:16,471 --> 00:06:20,538
We have rice last in Korea,
but they start with it here.

158
00:06:20,605 --> 00:06:22,705
REGARDLESS OF THE ORDER,
IT LOOKS JUST AS DELICIOUS.

159
00:06:22,771 --> 00:06:24,005
[Woo-jung] It looks so good.

160
00:06:24,071 --> 00:06:25,571
It smells amazing.

161
00:06:25,638 --> 00:06:28,038
- You can smell that butter.
- [Billy] You smell the garlic?

162
00:06:28,105 --> 00:06:29,105
Yes, I love garlic.

163
00:06:29,171 --> 00:06:30,538
REACTING TO THE GARLIC SMELL
LIKE A TRUE KOREAN

164
00:06:30,605 --> 00:06:32,905
BILLY GATHERS THE COOKED RICE
INTO THE CENTER

165
00:06:32,971 --> 00:06:34,705
[Woo-jung] Is something special
being made?

166
00:06:34,771 --> 00:06:35,738
[laughs]

167
00:06:35,805 --> 00:06:36,971
EVERYONE FULL OF ANTICIPATION

168
00:06:37,038 --> 00:06:38,471
Is it coming together now?

169
00:06:38,538 --> 00:06:40,605
A DIP IN THE MIDDLE TO CREATE…

170
00:06:40,671 --> 00:06:42,671
- [Woo-jung] It's a heart.
- [Billy in English] One more thing…

171
00:06:44,638 --> 00:06:47,005
[all exclaiming]

172
00:06:47,071 --> 00:06:48,605
[in Korean] It's beating hard.

173
00:06:48,671 --> 00:06:51,538
A TOTAL CROWD-PLEASER

174
00:06:51,605 --> 00:06:53,338
I love this place, Seo-jin.

175
00:06:53,405 --> 00:06:54,971
It's just my style.

176
00:06:55,038 --> 00:06:57,138
I KNEW YOU'D LIKE IT

177
00:06:57,205 --> 00:07:00,305
- [Billy speaking in English]
- [rhythmic tapping]

178
00:07:00,371 --> 00:07:02,705
MASTERFUL PACING

179
00:07:02,771 --> 00:07:04,871
[in Korean] When this part airs,

180
00:07:04,938 --> 00:07:07,905
2PM's "Heartbeat"
would be a good soundtrack.

181
00:07:07,971 --> 00:07:09,771
Let's buy the rights.
How much will it cost?

182
00:07:09,838 --> 00:07:11,071
EXCITEDLY RECOMMENDING A 17-YEAR-OLD SONG

183
00:07:11,138 --> 00:07:12,638
[Woo-jung] It's a great place for a date.

184
00:07:12,705 --> 00:07:15,905
- It would be an easy way to break the ice.
- [Dae-ju] It would.

185
00:07:15,971 --> 00:07:17,238
[Woo-jung] This tastes so good. Try it.

186
00:07:17,305 --> 00:07:18,738
FINALLY TRYING THE HEART FRIED RICE

187
00:07:18,805 --> 00:07:21,138
- Oh, I love the smokiness.
- [Dae-ju] Mmm.

188
00:07:21,205 --> 00:07:23,205
The garlic butter is amazing.

189
00:07:23,271 --> 00:07:24,471
[Woo-jung] It's so good.

190
00:07:25,005 --> 00:07:27,905
How could it not be?
Think of what it's made of.

191
00:07:27,971 --> 00:07:30,271
You can't go wrong
with butter, soy sauce, and salt.

192
00:07:30,338 --> 00:07:31,171
EXCITED RANTING

193
00:07:31,238 --> 00:07:34,605
NEW VEGETABLES ON THE GRIDDLE

194
00:07:34,671 --> 00:07:37,505
CAREFULLY MAKING AN ONION TOWER…

195
00:07:37,571 --> 00:07:38,838
What could that be?

196
00:07:38,905 --> 00:07:40,071
[amusing music playing]

197
00:07:40,138 --> 00:07:42,271
[in English]

198
00:07:42,338 --> 00:07:44,071
- [in Korean] A volcano.
- [Woo-jung] What?

199
00:07:44,138 --> 00:07:45,538
- It's a volcano.
- [all exclaiming]

200
00:07:45,605 --> 00:07:47,138
SHOOTING FLAMES

201
00:07:47,205 --> 00:07:50,538
- [in English] Volcano!
- [clanging]

202
00:07:50,605 --> 00:07:52,838
[in Korean] They even have
lighting effects. [laughs]

203
00:07:53,405 --> 00:07:55,405
[Billy mimics chugging]

204
00:07:55,471 --> 00:07:56,871
THE TRAIN IS CHUGGING

205
00:07:56,938 --> 00:07:59,371
TRAIN COMPLETE!

206
00:07:59,438 --> 00:08:02,638
CHUGGING ALONG

207
00:08:02,705 --> 00:08:06,938
WE DIDN'T EXPECT TO SEE A GRIDDLE TRAIN

208
00:08:07,705 --> 00:08:10,405
APPLAUSE

209
00:08:10,471 --> 00:08:13,605
PROUD BENIHANA PROMOTER

210
00:08:13,671 --> 00:08:14,871
[Woo-jung] This is so funny.

211
00:08:14,938 --> 00:08:17,938
THE END OF A PERFECT PERFORMANCE

212
00:08:18,005 --> 00:08:21,271
I should have come here
for my daughter's 7th birthday.

213
00:08:21,338 --> 00:08:23,271
She would have loved it.

214
00:08:23,338 --> 00:08:24,671
[Dae-ju] The train chugged along.

215
00:08:24,738 --> 00:08:26,471
- [Woo-jung] I did not see that coming.
- [Dae-ju] Right?

216
00:08:26,538 --> 00:08:28,271
[Woo-jung] We ordered lobster?

217
00:08:28,338 --> 00:08:29,405
This must be the one.

218
00:08:29,471 --> 00:08:31,205
- [Yung-suk] Is it the Ocean Treasure?
- [Woo-jung] Yes.

219
00:08:31,271 --> 00:08:34,405
BILLY SKILLFULLY CUTS THE SHRIMP TAILS

220
00:08:34,471 --> 00:08:37,138
- How can that not taste good?
- [Woo-jung] It's impossible.

221
00:08:37,205 --> 00:08:38,538
[in English]

222
00:08:38,605 --> 00:08:39,738
FLIP

223
00:08:39,804 --> 00:08:41,205
[Dae-ju] Whoa! [laughs]

224
00:08:42,471 --> 00:08:44,005
Whoa! [laughs]

225
00:08:44,071 --> 00:08:45,638
[in Korean] What was that?

226
00:08:45,705 --> 00:08:47,338
It went on the hat.

227
00:08:48,005 --> 00:08:49,271
TAILS FLYING INTO THE HAT

228
00:08:49,338 --> 00:08:51,538
[in English] I got one more. Double.

229
00:08:51,605 --> 00:08:54,505
A SHRIMP SHOW YOU CAN'T TAKE YOUR EYES OFF

230
00:08:57,771 --> 00:08:59,405
AN UNFORTUNATE MISS…

231
00:08:59,471 --> 00:09:02,871
[in Korean] This isn't
a good place for a date.

232
00:09:02,938 --> 00:09:05,605
You can't really look at each other.

233
00:09:05,671 --> 00:09:07,605
[Woo-jung] But it's perfect
for breaking the ice.

234
00:09:07,671 --> 00:09:09,038
- [Dae-ju] I agree.
- [Woo-jung] Yes.

235
00:09:09,105 --> 00:09:10,705
It's great for breaking the ice

236
00:09:10,771 --> 00:09:12,571
but not so great for conversation.

237
00:09:12,638 --> 00:09:14,305
You can't stop watching the show.

238
